      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification via method of manufactured solutions (MMS) for Navier-Stokes and hemolysis transport equations.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification performed for Navier-Stokes equations demonstrating expected second-order convergence. Hemolysis transport scalar equation verified only via grid refinement study, not MMS. Partial compliance at required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI; mesh convergence demonstrated on at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study performed; GCI for hemolysis index is 12.3% at operating point 3 (highest shear), exceeding the 5% target. Discretization error remains a credibility gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid properties, temperature, hematocrit, pump speed) documented with uncertainty bounds; conditions match COU operating envelope within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Bench test used porcine blood at 37°C with 35% hematocrit. COU specifies human blood at 37°C with 40–45% hematocrit. Fluid property mismatch introduces unquantified hemolysis model bias. Temperature controlled to ±0.5°C but hematocrit deviation not bounded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) computed for hemolysis index at all 5 operating points; metric accounts for experimental and numerical uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error reported at 18.4%; validation metric u_val not computed because experimental uncertainty bounds are incomplete (no repeat measurements at 2 of 5 operating points). Systematic over-prediction at high-speed conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Hemolysis index QoI directly corresponds to clinical endpoint; Lagrangian particle tracking stress exposure time demonstrated to correlate with in-vivo hemolysis outcomes.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is a direct surrogate for clinical hemolysis. However, the power-law model exponents were calibrated on Couette flow data and have not been validated for complex three-dimensional rotor-stator interaction flows. Relevance gap identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
